oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: The May Queen's Court at Columbia Institute
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Group portrait of several unidentified girls posed outside of the Columbia Institute. Text at the bottom of the photograph indicates they are part of The May Queen's Court. Many are holding flowers, and a small child holds a flag with the letters "CI" next to the girl standing on the top step.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Group portraits; Students; Manners & customs
